  "text": "Prostate cancer tissue microarray (TMA) slides were designated TMA 85 (primary and bone) and TMA 142 (primary, lymph node, and liver). TMAs were prepared as previously described [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue blocks with tumor samples were previously identified by a pathologist and processed as instructed by the IRB. Prostate tissue samples were taken from the radical prostatectomy series and the University of Michigan SPORE Rapid Autopsy Program [CITATION_3] . Tumors were staged and graded using the Gleason system (26). All tissue sections were reviewed by two board certified GU pathologists (RS, LK) and scored for stain intensity (0-3), percent positivity, and subcellular location.",
